Robert de Bercroft complains of Thomas Slater of a plea of tres- pass and contempt against the Statute. And whereupon he com- plains that the said Thomas, here at Nottingham, on Saturday next after the feast of Saint Michael last past, made a covenant with him that he would serve him in the craft of a slater from the said Saturday until all the houses of the said plaintiff were sufficiently tiled to the value of Ios. 5d.; and he did not come to his service, unjustly and against the form of the Statute, and to the grievous damage of the said plaintiff of 20s. Which Thomas came; and acknowledged the aforesaid trespass‚ and put himself in mercy. And he made fine with our Lord the King: and the damages are taxed at 4d. 1306, ro. for. 1.
